-# `averages` is present from `head_data` / `show.json` when available. Planning wait/visit header blocks read `routes_wait_time` / `routes_visits_duration` inside it. `show.json` may still pass root `wait_time` / `visits_duration` for first paint — never use `averages ||= nil` (NameError if the local was not passed).
- averages = local_assigns.fetch(:averages, nil)
- planning_route_errors = local_assigns.fetch(:planning_route_errors, nil)
- header_order = planning_header_block_order
.row.route-data.route-header.display-ui-planning-head{style: 'display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap;'}
  - header_order.each_with_index do |key, idx|
    - partial = Preferences::Catalog.header_block_partial('planning', key)
    - next if partial.blank?
    = render partial: partial, locals: local_assigns.merge(averages: averages, ui_order: idx)
- if planning_route_errors&.dig(:route_error)
  .row
    = render partial: 'routes/route_error_messages', locals: { flags: planning_route_errors }
